{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/edge-computation-101-2c1823656940", "time": 1683011144.931937, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/edge-computation-101-2c1823656940/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Edge Computation 101. Have a basic understanding of Edge\u2026 | by Renu Khandelwal | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Edge Computation 101", "description": "As per Cisco estimates, nearly 850 Zettabytes (ZB) of data will be generated each year outside the cloud by 2021, and IoT devices will make a substantial portion of that data. For using the data\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [], "all_paragraphs": ["In this article, we will discuss", "As per Cisco estimates, nearly 850 Zettabytes (ZB) of data will be generated each year outside the cloud by 2021, and IoT devices will make a substantial portion of that data.", "For using the data generated by IoT devices effectively, data should be communicated across devices seamlessly for real-time computation and inference, resulting in better data security and reduced latencies.", "Edge Computing, Fog computing, and Cloud computing address a lot of the challenges in terms of performance, security, and cost-effectiveness. Based on data computation, analytics, and storage needs of an organization, design a well-balanced mix of Edge computation, Fog computation, and Cloud computation.", "Edge Computation is done directly on the devices connected to the sensors or actuators where the data is generated.", "What is the difference between Edge computing, Fog computing, and cloud computing?", "The difference between Edge, Fog, and Cloud computation is based on the location where the data is generated, processed, accessed, and intelligence applied.", "Why should you use Edge computing?", "There are several benefits of Edge computation", "Edge computation is used when there is a need for reduced latencies to process the data. If you need quick data processing, then it should be performed as close as possible to the source of data generation to avoid any latencies due to data transfer.", "Autonomous vehicles, the Internet of Things, Voice Assistants, Predictive maintenance of machines or services, Traffic Management, etc. implements Edge computation.", "For example, Voice Assistants take your voice commands, apply Automatic Speech Recognition using Deep NLP to convert the speech to text, and also applying the language context, searches the web, and delivers the results. All of this happens at the Edge.", "What are your options for Edge computing?", "There are three categories of Edge AI hardware based on their technical architecture.", "So how to decide what type of computation you should use?", "Edge Computation: If you are looking for faster data processing, higher inference time, high data security with lower bandwidth to no internet connectivity, then Edge computation is the best option.", "Cloud Computation: If you are looking for data processing needs anywhere and at any time. Your data processing and storage needs are different at different times and like to scale up and scale down data processing resources; in that case, cloud suits your needs better.", "Fog Computation: If you have lots of Edge devices and need centralized data processing with reasonable data security and still having high inference time. Also, when internet connectivity is not very stable or has low bandwidth, then Fog computing servers your need.", "Based on your data processing or inference needs, network connectivity, and data security requirements, you can select either one or a mix of computing needs.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "A Technology Enthusiast who constantly seeks out new challenges by exploring cutting-edge technologies to make the world a better place!"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F2c1823656940&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=